
                              Developer guidelines

                                 Arni Magnusson

                                  23 Sep 2010



-------------
PREREQUISITES
-------------

Windows: SVN, Rtools, LaTeX

Linux: none



-------------
EDIT FUNCTION
-------------

1 Check out a working copy

    svn co svn+ssh://scm.r-forge.r-project.org/svnroot/hafroassmt/pkg local

2 Edit local/R/foo.R

3 Edit local/man/foo.Rd

4 Add entries to ChangeLog

5 Make a copy of 'local' directory and call it 'hafroAssmt'

6 Check package

    R CMD check hafroAssmt

7 If all tests are passed, delete 'hafroAssmt' and 'hafroAssmt.Rcheck'

8 Check SVN status inside 'local' directory

    svn st

9 If everything looks correct, commit changes to repository,

    svn ci

  adding a log entry (without final newline)



----------------
ADD NEW FUNCTION
----------------

1 Check out a working copy

    svn co svn+ssh://scm.r-forge.r-project.org/svnroot/hafroassmt/pkg local

2 Copy foo.R to local/R

3 Copy foo.Rd to local/man

4 Add entries to ChangeLog

5 Make a copy of 'local' directory and call it 'hafroAssmt'

6 Check package

    R CMD check hafroAssmt

7 If all tests are passed, delete 'hafroAssmt' and 'hafroAssmt.Rcheck'

8 Add new files to project inside the 'local' directory

    svn add R/foo.R
    svn add man/foo.Rd

9 Check SVN status inside 'local' directory

    svn st

10 If everything looks correct, commit changes to repository,

    svn ci

  adding a log entry (without final newline)
